<subSubSection id="D08610A3486F77E0F27CB5FCBC49CA61" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="5889B3A4BA6F11CFBB97FE6142C7C7E1" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A3E54D323B27EB232FA8B95420B2E029" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
[Italy], Auf Kalkconglommerat in Villa Lagarina bei Roveredo in 
<normalizedToken id="D80B02040ACAF83A89B58E8315AFCB28" originalValue="Südtirol">Suedtirol</normalizedToken>
, 1.5.1883, P. Strasser (M-02039301!, holotype).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BF80A2585E2566CE85FFFE35337C52AA" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="description">
<paragraph id="B3DC84E27AD8CBB7436E76235A328869" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C43592067C030A9AC686B8610052D5FA" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
Prothallus not seen. Thallus whitish-grey, endolithic. Perithecia 0.15-0.38 mm, (3/4)-1-immersed, leaving deep pits in the rock. Involucrellum apical, ca. 50-90 mm thick, appressed to the exciple. Exciple ca. 0.22-0.26 mm in diam., wall pale brown to dark brown. Periphysoids ca. 30-50 
<normalizedToken id="F836D2E1919ED6F44BFAAE0886058010" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.5-2.5 mm, branching. Asci ca. 88-95 
<normalizedToken id="8FFE54A7173A0489F9AB27CEECEB015D" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
26-28 mm, 8-spored. Ascospores 0-septate, (23.6-)24.5-26.6-28.8(-30.2) 
<normalizedToken id="310D1A016FF69A4F7D1C6EA1BA5D6546" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
(10.1-)10.4-11.4-12.4(-13.7) mm (n = 17).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F8562C8466059627BAC7CFE200378DBE" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="notes">
<paragraph id="0CB69B6F96F893AF7580FBBFEC009229" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="04AA71F77DAD77B623396BA9EA5CF940" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
The species may differ from the 
<taxonomicName id="BBC555F2CAC4D3E710D2995CA1D79A75" genus="V." lsidName="V. devergens" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="devergens">
<emphasis id="82C9C7EE46F15746D8FD109BFA9B9B97" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. devergens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="D526FC960722A3951289C526B3CEB99B" genus="V." lsidName="V. subtilis" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="subtilis">
<emphasis id="0716E1CF407F1CA2583443CD76B97BA1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. subtilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complexes by mostly fully immersed perithecia and from the 
<taxonomicName id="0469ABF6EBF4D929F22A7CDCB02C69C5" genus="V." lsidName="V. subtilis" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="subtilis">
<emphasis id="A2E779015B7842B9AD9A97C5278190D5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. subtilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex by slightly larger perithecia and a thicker involucrellum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
